"I started to study English for listen Gura's stream"



I started to study English to listen to Gura's streams



Changing "to study" to "studying" or changing "to listen" to "so I could listen" will make it sound nicer but it's ok that way.



"this is really good stream ever"



"Really good" and "ever" have conflicting meanings (sort of). "Really good" still means similar or better things probably exist. Ever implies an absolute (for all time). Ever is usually combined with best. "This is the best movie ever!"



You can just say "this is a really good stream" or you can say "this is the perfect stream for me". Perfect can imply serendipity.



I hope this is helpful.

text: ¬†@miloXZ¬† it has to do with the word "Maho", which can be translated as demon or magic (the most typical translation for this word is Magic, however in Konosuba it should have been translated as Demon, this is an understandable translation error in the light novel as the typica; word for Demon is Akuma, which is not used in Konosuba for the crimson demons).  Interestingly the Mushoku Tensei light novel had this same translation issue with the "Demon God Laplace", the Demon continent and Demon Races... as technically depending on the context all these names could be translated as the "Magic " (again Akuma was not used in any of those names just Maho)... All from the same light novel.  It was hundreds of chapters into the story before the various translators chose to use "Demon" for Maho in Mushoku Tensei, and I'm still not sure they were right, sort of curious on the translation the Anime will chose to use, as I'm 90% sure the "Demon God Laplace" title probably should be the "Magic God Laplace", even if the other demon translations (continent, and races) was correct.
